(127, 'Field Test Report: Airborne Failure Assessment', 'During the most recent aerial trial, we encountered an unforeseen malfunction in the flight stabilization mechanism, resulting in an abrupt descent. Preliminary analysis suggests that the enchantment on the lift harness was improperly calibrated, leading to a cascading series of failures mid-flight.'),
